				<h6 class="text-header">m.v.p on the m-i-c</h6>
			I've always loved rap. Growing up, albums like Black Star, Illmatic, and Organix changed my life. So it's no surprise that when I discovered Rap Genius, I was pumped to finally have a way to decrypt some of the tricker bars. As if that wasn't enough, the Rap Genius platform soon became the GENIUS platform, and suddenly, poetry, political speeches, and the news were made just as easy to understand as the rap albums I listened to as a kid. I'm the kind of guy who reads through every annotation in a David Foster Wallace book, so it's no grand claim to say that I love annotations.
